      <abstract>
        <p>Vietnam says there are six widows for every widower in country, result of years of war, lifespan differences and higher remarriage rate for men (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A government official said there were six widows for every widower in Vietnam, a result of years of war, longer lifespans for women and a higher remarriage rate for men. He said there were 2.93 million widows and 470,000 widowers in a population of 79 million people.</p>
        <p>Seth Mydans (NYT)</p>
      </block>
